The paper deals with compression and duplication of image data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The proposed method involves exploiting the shift sensitivity of compression algorithms, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.IR). The paper also discusses optimization techniques for the compression process, which is a common topic in graphics (cs.GR) research.
